    @SuppressWarningsPrefix({"calledmethods","builder","object.construction","objectconstruction"})
@SupportedOptions({"useValueChecker","countFrameworkBuildCalls","disableBuilderFrameworkSupports","disableReturnsReceiver"})
@StubFiles({"DescribeImages.astub","GenerateDataKey.astub"})
public class CalledMethodsChecker
extends org.checkerframework.common.accumulation.AccumulationChecker
    The Called Methods Checker tracks the methods that have definitely been called on an object. One common use case for the Called Methods Checker is to specify safe combinations of options to builder or builder-like interfaces, preventing objects from being instantiated incompletely.

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static java.lang.String COUNT_FRAMEWORK_BUILD_CALLS
      If this option is supplied, count the number of analyzed calls to build() in supported builder frameworks and print it when analysis is complete.
      static java.lang.String DISABLE_BUILDER_FRAMEWORK_SUPPORTS
      This option disables the support for (and therefore the automated checking of) code that uses the given builder frameworks.
      static java.lang.String DISABLE_RETURNS_RECEIVER
      Some use cases for the Called Methods Checker do not involve checking fluent APIs, and in those cases disabling the Returns Receiver Checker using this flag will make the Called Methods Checker run much faster.
      static java.lang.String USE_VALUE_CHECKER
      If this option is supplied, use the Value Checker to reduce false positives when analyzing calls to the AWS SDK.

        public static final java.lang.String COUNT_FRAMEWORK_BUILD_CALLS

      • DISABLE_BUILDER_FRAMEWORK_SUPPORTS

        public static final java.lang.String DISABLE_BUILDER_FRAMEWORK_SUPPORTS
        This option disables the support for (and therefore the automated checking of) code that uses the given builder frameworks. Useful when a user **only** wants to enforce specifications on custom builder objects (such as the AWS SDK examples).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
